The Telegraph - Calcutta

 Soccer clashes

Budapest: Two British fans were in a critical condition in a Budapest hospital on Friday after clashes between Millwall and Ferencvaros fans before Thursday?s Uefa Cup tie, the British Embassy said. 

?Neither is in a life-threatening situation, their condition is serious but stable and they are in intensive care,? said an embassy spokesman . 

Meanwhile, in Belgrade, more than a dozen fans and police were injured in fighting after a Uefa Cup match between Red Star Belgrade and Zenit St Petersburg on Thursday. Fourteen people were injured when fighting broke out in the Red Star?s Marakana stadium following the team?s 6-1 aggregate defeat by the Russian side. (Agencies) 

